<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">My guild (and most of the people I group with) do tradeskills, so we do take the tradeskill items into account when we set up looting rules. But we only NBG for the toons who are there when it drops; if none of the toons present is doing that skill, the item is lottoed like any other loot that won't be used by the toons present. If something drops and someone wants it for an alt, they can trade for it or work something out if they don't win the roll.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
