<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I've only been in a couple groups so far but we just went on lotto as it seems much faster/easier.  I 2-box and when I do I usually decline the lotto on 1 of the chars.  There was a situation where I was playing my chanter and an adept 1 dropped that my summoner could have used and since there were no summoners in the group they let me have that one as they were all about the NBG and were obviously very trusting too (it was the adept 1 pet which ROCKS).
<br />

<br />
While it would be nice to have alts be considered, I am in a similar position where I have 4 now above lvl10 all of which do their own tradeskills too - so that's getting to be a bit much for your groups to consider.  If there is an item/book whatever I could use on an alt I would defer if someone in the group could use it and just go for stuff the 2 chars I'm playing at the time could use, and when 2-box I would decline/pass on lotto loot on one of the chars to make it a fair and equal chance of loot distribution.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
