<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">This weekend I was in a group as my druid and a druid adept spell dropped.  The tank won it, and then asked the group "Who needs ____?"
<br />

<br />
I said "It's a druid spell."
<br />

<br />
Nothing.
<br />

<br />
"I need it."
<br />

<br />
Nothing.
<br />

<br />
"Can I trade you something for it?"
<br />

<br />
Nothing.
<br />

<br />
A couple minutes later, I asked again, and he said "Sorry it's for a friend."
<br />

<br />
Ugh.  Now we're farming for all his friends, too?  And we're not talking tradeskills stuff either.  This was for a certain class - mine!  No way he could use it.
<br />

<br />
I then realized that his group tell asking who needed it was probably meant for his guild.
<br />

<br />
I quietly excused myself a minute later.  I wanted to say "then your friend can heal you too," but I decided to just get out and call it a night.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
